66 {
67 std::stringstream debug_message;

84 } else {
85 // clean report dbs
86 boost::filesystem::remove(db_path);

ebi::TEST_CASE ( "RecordCache tests: across chromosomes" )

Definition at line 192 of file record_cache_test.cpp.

192 : across chromosomes")
193 {
194 vcf::RecordCache cache{2};
195
196 cache.check_duplicates(build_mock_record({"2", 102, "A", {"T"}}));
197 cache.check_duplicates(build_mock_record({"2", 103, "A", {"T"}}));
198
199 SECTION("One duplicate in another chromsome")
200 {
201 // bug EVA-1950
202 // the chromosome "10" is likely to appear *after* "2" in a VCF, but "10" is lexicographically lower
203 CHECK( count_duplicates(cache, {"10", 107, "C", {"T"}}) == 0);
204 CHECK( count_duplicates(cache, {"10", 107, "C", {"T"}}) == 2); // duplicate, undetected before EVA-1950
205 }
206 }

ebi::TEST_CASE ( )

49 : capacity==1")
50 {
51 vcf::RecordCache cache{1};
52
53 cache.check_duplicates(build_mock_record({100, "A", {"T"}}));
54
55 SECTION("There's no duplicate") {
56 CHECK( count_duplicates(cache, {101, "A", {"T"}}) == 0 );
57 }
58 SECTION("No duplicate detected because capacity is too small") {
59 CHECK( count_duplicates(cache, {101, "A", {"T"}}) == 0 );

74 }

ebi::TEST_CASE ( "RecordCache tests: symbolic duplicates" )

Definition at line 161 of file record_cache_test.cpp.

161 : symbolic duplicates")
162 {
163 vcf::RecordCache cache{0};
164
165 cache.check_duplicates(build_mock_record({100, "A", {"T"}}));
166 cache.check_duplicates(build_mock_record({101, "A", {"T"}}));
167 cache.check_duplicates(build_mock_record({103, "A", {"T"}}));
168 cache.check_duplicates(build_mock_record({107, "C", {"<INS>"}}));
169
170 SECTION("No symbolic duplicates")
171 {
172 CHECK( count_symbolic_duplicates(cache, {106, "A", {"T"}}) == 0 );
173 CHECK( count_symbolic_duplicates(cache, {99, "GA", {"GT", "C"}}) == 0 );
174 CHECK( count_symbolic_duplicates(cache, {103, "A", {"T"}}) == 0 );
175 CHECK( count_symbolic_duplicates(cache, {107, "C", {"<DEL>"}}) == 0 );
176 CHECK( count_symbolic_duplicates(cache, {108, "C", {"<INS>"}}) == 0 );
177 }
178
179 SECTION("One Symbolic Duplicate")
180 {
181 // Symbolic duplicate detected
182 CHECK( count_symbolic_duplicates(cache, {107, "C", {"<INS>"}}) == 2 );
183 }
184 SECTION("Symbolic Triplicates")
185 {
186 CHECK( count_symbolic_duplicates(cache, {107, "C", {"<INS>"}}) == 2 );
187 // the first occurrence of symbolic duplicate should not be reported again
188 CHECK( count_symbolic_duplicates(cache, {107, "C", {"<INS>"}}) == 1 );
189 }
190 }

ebi::TEST_CASE ( "RecordCache tests: unlimited capacity" )

Definition at line 122 of file record_cache_test.cpp.

122 : unlimited capacity")
123 {
124 vcf::RecordCache cache{0};
125
126 cache.check_duplicates(build_mock_record({100, "A", {"T"}}));

129 cache.check_duplicates(build_mock_record({103, "A", {"T"}}));
130 cache.check_duplicates(build_mock_record({104, "A", {"T"}}));
131 cache.check_duplicates(build_mock_record({105, "A", {"T"}}));
132
133 SECTION("There's no duplicate") {

135 }
136
137 SECTION("Duplicate detected because there's no capacity limitation") {
138 // This is not going to throw because capacity is 1, we would need a bigger cache.
139 CHECK( count_duplicates(cache, {99, "GA", {"GT", "C"}}) == 2 );
140 }
141 SECTION("One simple duplicate") {
142 CHECK( count_duplicates(cache, {103, "A", {"T"}}) == 2 );

146 }
147 SECTION("Triplicate")
148 {
149 CHECK( count_duplicates(cache, {100, "GA", {"GT", "C"}}) == 2 );
150 // the first occurrence should not be reported again
151 CHECK( count_duplicates(cache, {100, "GA", {"GT"}}) == 1 );
152 }
153 SECTION("Symbolic Duplicates")
154 {
155 CHECK( count_duplicates(cache, {107, "C", {"<INS>"}}) == 0 );
156 // Not a duplicate, hence not detected

◆ test_normalization()

std::pair< std::vector< vcf::RecordCore >, std::vector< vcf::RecordCore > > ebi::test_normalization ( std::function< std::vector< vcf::RecordCore >(const vcf::Record &record)> normalize_function,
TestMultiRecord orig,
std::vector< TestRecord > results )

This helper function takes a simplified variant (2nd argument, TestMultiRecord) that may be multiallelic, and returns its normalization (performed with a user provided function, 1st argument) along with the expected result (3rd argument, vector<TestRecord>) in a comparable way (both as vectors of RecordCore). Example:

auto comparison = test_normalization(vcf::normalize, {1000, "T", {"G", "A"}}, {{1000, "T", "G"}, {1000, "T", "A"}}); CHECK((comparison.first) == (comparison.second));
